headline: Ukraine-related demand sends US arms exports to record in 2024
summary: Sales of U.S. military equipment to foreign governments in 2024 rose 29% to a record $318.7 billion, the U.S. State Department said on Friday, as countries sought to replenish stocks sent to Ukraine...
